It's cozy here, and I'm a happy guy.  I've been up all night, but I've got everything done, so I feel good about it.  The sunrise is going to happen around Seven, and I'm going to go up to the roof of the Parking Garage and enjoy it.  I just feel pretty damn blissful. : )

There was this one time back in the old days when cabbage was three cents a pound, even though nobody really cared for it, it was abundant is all I'm saying, that young Frederick Jones went down to his brother's place, his brother Sal that is, not his brother Jimmy, Jimmy had died in the war, and anyway he went down to his brother Sal's place which was rested up against a large oak tree. That tree was just about all there was keeping that shack from falling into the old emerald mine owned and operated by it's sole propertier, Fred's brother Sal. Now, Sal wasn't a wealthy man by eartly standards, for you see, even though an emerald is a precious stone, it is an expensive business, removin' them from the earth and findin' people who would actually be wanting the emeralds to sell them to, and it really was a buyer's market then. But Ol' Sal had what counted, he had a comfy bed and and an old yellow dog to keep him company and at the end of the day he had a stool to rest his feet on iff'n he so desired. So anyway, Fred comes along and he knocks on his brother's door (not that it was a nescessary act, the dog had smelled him a mile away, but it was what one does in polite society) and his broter opens up and says Hello Fred What're you doin' here and Fred says Well Sal I've come to tell you that Jimmy's dead, he's been shot in the trenches and that the funeral's on Sunday in the big old Graveyard down on Clementine street, and that you should wear your sunday best, not that I needed to tell you, it bein' Sunday and all, but I Ma asked me to anyway. now, Sal was just about speechless and neither brother would have said anything for a while if the dog hadn't started barking at something out the window so Fred and Sal go over to the window and take a look outside and they see the biggest fish they ever did see flopping around outside (it must have been dropped by a bear who decided that he didn't want the thing, as bears were more likely to be picky back then, they bein' the dominant species and all) so they go to check it out an' al says to Fred it must be a magic fish, and maybe it'll give us three wishes if we were to catch it and drop it off at the old pond, and Sal says that's all well and good for you to say, but it is a mighty big fish and I think that it would make a mighty fine meal for the wake, as Jimmy always liked Carp and that seems to be what that is right there and I'll be damned if they both weren't right because what they had in front of them was a Magic Carp. Before the brother could go up to the fish for one purpose or the other, an eagle swooped down from the heavens and picked it up. That eagle took the carp, flew it half-way around the world and dropped it onto a painting in Germany that wa still drying, completely destroying the work of art. It's creator woke with a start and with a 'God in Heaven!', he shot out of his bed, handdlebar moustache twitching in rage. This will make me fail out of art school! GOD DAMMIT! I BET IT WAS THOSE JEWISH FISH MONGORS UPSTAIRS! I HATE THEM SO. THEY HAVE BEEN MEAN TO ME EVER SINCE THEY DISCOVERED THAT I WAS A VEGETARIAN AND WOULD NOT PURCHASE THEIR SEA-MEATS. That man went on to become the Leader of his nation, all thanks to the Magic Carp.




END
Well I've been up all night again, and I'm not done with my lab.  My numbers keep coming out negative, and they aren't supposed to be.  D:

Huh.  I haven't used this in a while.  I'm just feelin' kinda fat and ugly and perfectly sound.  Eh.  Missing home, feeling irresponsible and like I'm letting ADD take too much claim for my wacky antics.  I have to put a lock on my internet spending.  I don't think I'm eating right, either.  I don't want to go to the Gym by myself.  6.  I  am afraid that I will sleep through the Majority of my Orgo class next semester, a class that is taught by the chair of the Chem Department (and the father of my neighbor on the right).  I haven't yet written a satisfactory lab report, but My results are good.  I always leave them for the last night, and end up starting at eleven or later.  You just lost The Game.  I traded Ten dollars worth of quarters for cash when my roommate needed quarters to do his wash, but now I am out of quarters.  I shattered a bottle on my floor the other day.  My bed is always covered by stuff during the day, which I shift off of it at night.  I am afraid that I am not a good roommate.  I have been good about changing my sheets and washing my clothes.  I miss my kitties.  End.
:D  It's quarter of Four and I can go to Bed!  YAY!

1.) Where were you when the ball dropped for 2006? I was at Meg's party! 2.) How did you get the idea for your livejournal name? I had a green shirt that I really loved. 3) What are you listening to right now? The "Thank You For Smoking" Soundtrack. It's fun. 4.) Has the death of a celebrity ever made you cry? I'm certain they have, but none in recent memory. Steve Irwin did make me really sad. Oh, right, The lady that did Lamb Chop! 5.) What underwear are you wearing? I am wearing gray boxer-breif hybrids with horizontal gray stripes. 6.) Do you live in a zoo? Nope. Not anymore! 7.) What did you do this morning? What is your favorite frozen treat? Dark Chocolate Klondike Bars, 29.) How many tattoos/piercing do you have? None! 30.) What are your favorite stores? The Outer Limits, Gourmet Pottery, and the Internet! 31.) Are you thirsty right now? Kinda. 32.) Can you imagine yourself ever getting married? Oh, god I hope so. 33.) Who is someone you haven't seen in a while and miss? MIke, AlONg wIth All of my ClosEsT pAls. 34.) What did you do last night? Ben, Chamith and Rob came over, so we played around, played some games and hung out. My roommate sat out in the hall ;_; I keep telling him that it's his room too and if he wants something changed, all he has to do is say so! 35.) Do you care what people think about you? Yes. Please tell me what you think of me! 36.) Have you ever done something to instigate trouble? Not in recent Memory. 37) Do you like your nose? Until it gets to the end, i wish it were a little sharper. 38.) What color is your bedroom? White. 39.) When was the last time you worked out? Too long ago. I'm going to look into stuff here. 41.) Do you like pedicures? Well, I love to be petted, but me feet are awfully ticklish. 42.) Where do you live? 325 Bullock Hall, Clark University. 43.) Are you an aggressive driver? I don't think so. 44.) Who is your cell phone carrier? Verison. 47.) What is the one thing you'd want to change most about yourself? My boring past. 48.) What color is your car? Gold. Well, it's my mom's car, but I'm counting it. 49.) What do you smell like right now? Terrible! Well, not really, but how else could I respond to that question? 50.) What is your favorite color? Red, like a leaf in the fall. 51.) Do you like mustard? Yes, but only recently. 52.)What do you tell yourself when times get hard? Hey, it's fine. I can't stay sad or angry for very long anyway, so what's the point of dwelling on the negative? Gosh, those trees are pretty! 53.)Would you ever sky dive? I could. 54.)What do you sleep on? Paisley sheets on a space-foam mattress pad on a standard-issue college mattress. 55.)What character from a movie/TV most reminds you of yourself? Fry. You know, except for the awesome future world with the hot alien girlfriend. Ben is a robot though. 56.)Have you ever bid for something on ebay? Yes ;_; 57.) What do you think of Angelina Jolie being pregnant? DOES ANYBODY ELSE HERE LIKE ANGELINA JOLIE? 58.) Do you enjoy giving hugs? I love hugs. Sometimes I just want to hug everything. 59.) Would you consider yourself to be fashionable? No, but I like the way I dress. 60.) Do you own a digital camera? I had a keychain one, but I lost it. 61.)What celebrities have you been compared to? Mike Meyers, Mr. Bean, Harrison Ford and Michael Ian Black 62.)Who is your favorite Star Wars character? Han Solo. 63.)Does it annoy you when someone says they'll call but never do? Yeah, but it's not like I can't call them. 64.)What books, if any, have made you cry? A dumb Terry Brooks fantasy when the elf died when I was eleven. Seriously. 66.) Are you a jealous person? Yes, and I'm not proud of it. I mean, I don't know why someone would be, but I'm not. 67.)Do you ever feel guilty after eating meat? Yeah, especially if I don't finish it. 68.)What would your name have been if you had been born the opposite sex? Probably Anne. 69.)If you could date anyone at your school, who would it be? Well, no one at this school. 70.) Did you enjoy this survey? Yaks in the Mist
by Milky Puppy

Slowly, very slowly, I watched as the majestic yak emerged slowly from the gentle mist. I slowly let my eyes wander all over its body, I slowly noticed a fine mist on top of its fur. I slowly wandered over to it. Its mouth slowly formed a smile. I slowly raised my hand and slowly stroked its head. Slowly it raised its head and slowly said "Why are you doing everything so fucking slowly?", and it slowly sprinted off in the direction of Libya.

SO THERE I WAS, LYING IN BED, WHEN I HEARD THAT OMINOUS BUZZING THAT COULD ONLY REALLY HAVE COME FROM ONE THING, NO MATTER HOW MANY TIMES I TOLD MYSELF THAT IT WAS THE FRIDGE OR THE NEIGHBOR'S AIR-CONDITIONER. THE FUCKING THING DARES ME TO GET UP, IT LANDS ON MY NOSE, CAN YOU BELIEVE THAT? I JUMP OUT OF BED, TURN THE LIGHT ON, AND ASSUME A KARATE POSE. I CLOSED MY EYES UNTIL I HEARD IT AGAIN, AND STARTED CHASING AFTER IT. I PUNCHED IT A FEW TIMES, BUT WITH SUCH LITTLE MASS, IT WASN'T REALLY DAMAGED BY THAT. THE THING HAD A BRAIN, IT KNEW WHAT IT WAS DOING. IT LANDED ON MY MIRROR AND ON MY COMPUTER MONITOR. SERIOUSLY. BUT THAT'S NOT HOW IT GOT ME. I GOT A BIT FRAZZLED AFTER AN HOUR OF THIS, AND STARTED JUST CLAPPING ANYTIME IT CAME NEAR. AND THEN IT LANDED RIGHT ON MY CROTCH, AND FUCK ME IF I DIDN'T PUNCH MYSELF IN THE BOY BITS WITH ALL OF MY MIGHT. OW.
